==English==

===Etymology===
Old English ''[[sinu]]''

===Pronunciation===
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-ɪn|-ɪn]]

====Noun====
'''shin''' (pl. ''shins'')

# The front part of the leg below the knee; the front edge of the shin bone; the lower part of the leg; the shank.

====Translations====
*French: [[tibia]] {{m}}
*Polish: [[goleń]] {{f}}
*Portuguese: [[canela]] {{f}}

====Verb====
'''shin''' ([[shinned]], [[shinning]], [[shins]])

# To climb a mast, tree, rope, or the like, by embracing it alternately with the arms and legs, without help of steps, spurs, or the like; -- used with up; as, to '''shin''' up a mast.

====Synonyms====
* [[tibia]]

====Derived terms====
* [[shinny]]
* [[shin bone]]
* [[shin leaf]]
* [[shin splints]]

